SIMPLE: cowardly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cowardly
<hw>Cow"ard*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wanting courage;
basely or weakly timid or fearful; pusillanimous; spiritless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>cowardly</qex> rascals that ran from the battle.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Proceeding from fear of danger or other
consequences; befitting a coward; dastardly; base; <as>as,
<ex>cowardly</ex> malignity</as>.</def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>cowardly</qex> rashness of those who dare not look danger
in the face.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Timid; fearful; timorous; dastardly;
pusillanimous; recreant; craven; faint-hearted; chicken-hearted;
white-livered.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowardly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cowardly
<hw>Cow"ard*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In the manner of a
coward.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowardship</ent>⟦br⟧
